{"body": "My use case (i'm sure there are others):\r\nI have two hash: old_hash, new_hash (one is from a json api, the other a yaml file)\r\nI want to see what has changed (ie what's new in new_hash)\r\n```ruby \r\nwhat_was_added = new_hash - old_hash\r\nwhat_was_removed = old_hash - new_hash\r\n```\r\nI agree that commits to Hash should be examined very carefully. Maybe overwriting the \"-\" is an overreach. Let me know what you think.\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/16065617", "created_at": "2013-04-08T17:35:31Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10141#issuecomment-16065617", "updated_at": "2013-04-08T17:37:22Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10141, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/elfassy/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/elfassy/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/elfassy/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/elfassy", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/elfassy/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/elfassy", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/elfassy/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/ba7b4287fb72d3d7d8c56f5fca4c8bd9?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Feca8cafbe0ebbc5ffd761f8c3d297fa4.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/elfassy/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/elfassy/received_events", "gravatar_id": "ba7b4287fb72d3d7d8c56f5fca4c8bd9", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/elfassy/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "elfassy", "type": "User", "id": 311279, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/elfassy/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237e2e7bd3543c15100907a"}, "id": 16065617, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10141"}
